Police in Nakuru are pursuing their colleague for allegedly shooting his wife and four-year-old daughter to death following a domestic wrangle.
Constable Cosmas Kipchumba Biwott who is attached to the Weseges anti-stock theft unit in Subukia, is  said to have shot 26-year-old Jane Njoki in the head 20 times before turning the gun on his 4-year-old daughter, Shantel Nyambura.
According to Subukia OCPD Alex Ng’ang’a, the officer  used his colleague’s firearm to commit the crime  before he disappeared. 